{
  "plugin": "sshuttle",
  "version": "v0.2.6",
  "homepage": "https://github.com/jjo/kubectl-sshuttle",
  "description": "Manages a proxy pod in a Kubernetes cluster and tunnels traffic\nthrough it. Lets you reach IPs and subnets that are only accessible\nfrom inside the cluster network.\n\nThree transport modes:\n  default            — sshuttle locally, python+sshuttle in pod\n  --rushtle-server   — sshuttle locally, rushtle server in pod\n                       (works around kubectl-exec >1KB stdin\n                        truncation seen on tailscale-fronted clusters)\n  --rushtle          — rushtle on both ends, no sshuttle/python at all\n                       (linux+macos, requires root locally for NAT setup)\n\nDefault and --rushtle-server modes require sshuttle locally\n(pip install sshuttle). The bundled `rushtle` binary is used for\n--rushtle mode.\n",
